It is generally bad practice to catch `Exception` (`java.lang.Exception`). This is the &quot;root&quot; of all checked exceptions and the catch-block will be jumped into whenever any subclass of `Exception` is thrown.  
Just catch the concrete exception that you are expecting. (In this case `IllegalArgumentException`.)

Also you should not use exceptions to control the execution flow of your program. 

