If we are removing code from the `try` it almost seems like the try isn&#39;t worth having. The thing is, that try block was put there there for **some** reason. Try blocks are supposed to catch errors and it successfully did so, so obviously its doing something useful, and taking the code out of it feels like the wrong solution.

